{"title_page": "Pauline Johnson (immunologist)", "text_new": "{{short description|English immunologist and microbiologist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox scientist\n| name              = Pauline Johnson\n| image             = \n| image_size        = \n| alt               = \n| caption           = \n| birth_place       = [[Yorkshire]], England\n| death_date        = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place       = \n| resting_place     = \n| resting_place_coordinates = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} -->\n| citizenship       = \n| nationality       = \n| fields            = [[Immunology]]\n| workplaces        = [[University of British Columbia]]\n| alma_mater        = [[Liverpool University]]<br/>[[University of Dundee]]<br/>[[Oxford University]]<br/>[[Salk Institute]]\n| doctoral_advisor  = \n| academic_advisors = \n| doctoral_students = \n| notable_students  = \n| known_for         = Work on lymphocyte cell surface molecules and hyaluronan \n| author_abbrev_bot = \n| author_abbrev_zoo = \n| influences        = \n| influenced        = \n| awards            = \n| signature         = <!--(filename only)-->\n| signature_alt     = \n| website           = <!-- {{URL|www.example.com}} -->\n| footnotes         = \n}}\n'''Pauline Johnson''' is an English immunologist and microbiologist at the [[University of British Columbia]].<ref name=\"UBC\" /> Her research focuses on innate and adaptive immune mechanisms \u2014 in particular, the mobility of proteins in membranes, [[lymphocyte]] cell surface molecules, [[T cell]] [[cell signaling|signalling]], [[leukocyte]] adhesion, and [[macrophage]]s in lung [[inflammation]].<ref name=\"UBC\" />\n\n==Education==\nPauline Johnson was born in [[Yorkshire]], England. She earned a BSc in biochemistry from [[Liverpool University]] in 1980, and a Ph.D from the [[University of Dundee]] in 1983.<ref name=\"UBC\" /><ref name=\"III Institute Advisory Board\">{{Cite web | url=https://cihr-irsc.gc.ca/e/50755.html#pauline_johnson |title = III Institute Advisory Board Members \u2013 Biographies - CIHR}}</ref> Her Ph.D. project was to determine the lateral and rotational mobility of membrane components measured by fluorescence recovery after photobleaching and fluorescence depletion recovery.\n<ref>{{Cite journal\n | pmid = 6170530 \n| year = 1981\n| author1 = Johnson, P. & Garland, P. B.\n| title = Depolarisation of fluorescence depletion. A microscopic method for measuring rotational diffusion of membrane proteins on the surface of a single cell\n| journal = FEBS Lett\n| volume = 132\n| issue = 2\n| pages = 252\u2013256\n| doi = 10.1016/0014-5793(81)81172-6\n}}\n</ref>\n\nShe was a post-doctoral fellow at the [[Salk Institute]] in [[California]], US under the supervision of Professor Ian Trowbridge  and at the MRC Cellular Immunology Unit at the [[University of Oxford]], U.K. under the supervision of Professor Alan F. Williams<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/Alan-Frederick-Williams.-25-May-1945-\u2013-9-April-1992-Crumpton/b4574e3cec2e7e6d5fb1b2b602446868e64b4e44|title=Alan Frederick Williams. 25 May 1945 \u2013 9 April 1992 &#124; Semantic Scholar}}</ref> before joining the faculty at the University of British Columbia in 1991.<ref name=\"III Institute Advisory Board\" />\n\n==Career and research==\nJohnson helped to establish the function of [[CD45]] as a critical protein [[tyrosine phosphatase]] in [[T cell]] activation\n<ref>{{Cite journal\n | pmid = 1314815\n| year = 1992\n| author1 = Johnson, P., Ostergaard, H. L., Wasden, C. & Trowbridge, I. S.\n| title = Mutational analysis of CD45, a leukocyte specific tyrosine phosphatase.\n| journal = Journal of Biological Chemistry\n| volume = 267\n| issue = 12\n| pages = 8035\u20138041 \n| doi = \n}}\n</ref>\nand defined the mechanisms regulating the interactions of the cell adhesion molecule [[CD44]] with the matrix component, [[hyaluronan]].<ref>{{Cite journal\n | pmid = 9794764 \n| year = 1998\n| author1 = Maiti, A., Maki, G. & Johnson P. \n| title = TNF-\u03b1 induction of CD44-mediated leukocyte adhesion by sulfation\n| journal = Science\n| volume = 282\n| issue = 5390\n| pages = 941\u2013943 \n| doi = 10.1126/science.282.5390.941\n}}\n</ref>  \n\nHer research in 2020 uses mouse models of lung disease to study the function of [[macrophages]] and the cell matrix in infection, [[inflammation]], and [[cancer]].<ref name=\"UBC\">{{Cite web|url=http://lsi.ubc.ca/person/pauline-johnson/|title=Pauline Johnson &#124; Life Sciences Institute|website=lsi.ubc.ca}}</ref>\n\nShe held an MRC Scientist Award and was Co-Director of the Infection, Inflammation and Immunity Research Group at the Life Science Institute at UBC (2003-2009).<ref name=\"III Institute Advisory Board\" /> She has served multiple times on the [[CIHR]] Immunology and Transplantation panel, including as Scientific Officer, as well as on other national and international review panels. She is a member of the CIHR III Institute Advisory Board (III institute = Inflammation, infection and immunity CIHR Institute).<ref name=\"III Institute Advisory Board\" />\n\n==Fellowships and awards==\n* Cancer Research Institute Fellowship, American Cancer Research Institute, 1987\n* MRC Scientist Award, MRC of Canada, 1999-2004\n* Women in Science Award for Community Leadership and Scientific Excellence, Minerva Foundation for B.C. Women, 2013<ref>{{cite web |title=Announcing the Honourees for Women In\u2122 Science |date=12 November 2013 |url=https://minervabc.ca/announcing-the-honourees-for-women-in-science/ |publisher=Minerva BC}}</ref>\n\n==Publications==\n*{{Cite journal\n | pmid = 6170530 \n| year = 1981\n| author1 = Johnson, P. & Garland, P. B.\n| title = Depolarisation of fluorescence depletion. A microscopic method for measuring rotational diffusion of membrane proteins on the surface of a single cell\n| journal = FEBS Lett\n| volume = 132\n| issue = 2\n| pages = 252\u2013256\n| doi = 10.1016/0014-5793(81)81172-6\n}}\n\n*{{Cite journal\n | pmid = 3092111 \n| year = 1986\n| author1 = Johnson, P. & Williams, A. F.\n| title = Striking similarities between antigen receptor J pieces and sequence in the second chain of the murine CD8 antigen\n| journal = Nature\n| volume = 323\n| issue = 6083\n| pages = 74\u201376\n| doi = 10.1038/323074a0\n| bibcode = 1986Natur.323...74J\n}}\n\n*{{Cite journal\n | pmid = 1314815\n| year = 1992\n| author1 = Johnson, P., Ostergaard, H. L., Wasden, C. & Trowbridge, I. S.\n| title = Mutational analysis of CD45, a leukocyte specific tyrosine phosphatase.\n| journal = Journal of Biological Chemistry\n| volume = 267\n| issue = 12\n| pages = 8035\u20138041 \n| doi = \n}}\n\n*{{Cite journal\n | pmid = 9794764 \n| year = 1998\n| author1 = Maiti, A., Maki, G. & Johnson P. \n| title = TNF-\u03b1 induction of CD44-mediated leukocyte adhesion by sulfation\n| journal = Science\n| volume = 282\n| issue = 5390\n| pages = 941\u2013943 \n| doi = 10.1126/science.282.5390.941\n}}\n\n*{{Cite journal\n | pmid = 21471214 \n| year = 2011\n| author1 = Ruffell, B., Poon, G.F.T., Lee, S.S.M., Brown, K.L., Tjew, S-L., Cooper. J., & Johnson, P. \n| title = Differential use of chondroitin sulfate to regulate hyaluronan binding by CD44 in inflammatory and alternatively activated macrophages\n| journal = Journal of Biological Chemistry\n| volume = 286\n| issue = 22\n| pages = 19179\u201319190\n| doi = 10.1074/jbc.M110.200790\n| pmc = 3103297\n}}\n\n*{{Cite journal\n| pmid = 25926830 \n| year = 2015\n| author1 = Lee-Sayer, S.M., Dong, Y., Arif, A.A., Olsson, M., Brown, K.L, & Johnson, P. \n| title = The where, when, how, and why of hyaluronan binding by immune cells.\n| journal = Frontiers in Immunology\n| volume = 6\n| issue = \n| pages = 150\n| doi = 10.3389/fimmu.2015.00150\n| pmc = 4396519\n}}\n\n*{{Cite journal\n | pmid = 27007678 \n| year = 2016\n| author1 = Samarakoon, A., SHIM, Y. A., Dosanjh, M, Crickmer, M., Labont\u00e8-Raymond, C., Arif, A.A. & Johnson, P.\n| title = CD45 regulates GM-CSF, retinoic acid and T cell homing in intestinal inflammation.\n| journal = Mucosal Immunology\n| volume = 9\n| issue = 6\n| pages = 1514\u20131527\n| doi = 10.1038/mi.2016.23\n}}\n\n*{{Cite journal\n | pmid = 30555472 \n| year = 2018\n| author1 = Johnson, P., Arif, AA, Lee-Sayer, S.S.M., Dong, Y.\n| title = Hyaluronan and Its Interactions With Immune Cells in the Healthy and Inflamed Lung.\n| journal = Frontiers in Immunology\n| volume = 9\n| issue = \n| pages = 2787\n| doi = 10.3389/fimmu.2018.02787\n| pmc = 6281886\n}}\n\n*{{Cite journal\n| pmid = 32082314  \n| year = 2020\n| author1 = Dong, Y., Arif, AA., Guo, J., HA, Z., Lee-Sayer, SSM., Poon, GFT., Dosanjh, M., Roskelley, C., Huan, T., Johnson, P.\n| title = CD44 loss disrupts lung lipid surfactant homeostasis and exacerbates oxidized lipid-induced lung inflammation\n| journal = Frontiers in Immunology\n| volume = 11\n| issue = \n| pages = 29\n| doi = 10.3389/fimmu.2020.00029\n| pmc = 7002364\n}}\n\n==Refrences==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.microbiology.ubc.ca/research/labs/johnson/pi Johnson Lab]\n* {{google scholar id|HAlgVsIAAAAJ}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Johnson, Pauline}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Scientists from Yorkshire]]\n[[Category:Women immunologists]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Liverpool]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Dundee]]\n[[Category:20th-century English scientists]]\n[[Category:20th-century women scientists]]\n[[Category:21st-century English scientists]]\n[[Category:21st-century women scientists]]\n[[Category:English women biologists]]\n[[Category:English microbiologists]]\n[[Category:Women microbiologists]]\n[[Category:20th-century British biologists]]\n[[Category:21st-century British biologists]]\n[[Category:English expatriates in Canada]]\n[[Category:British expatriate academics in Canada]]\n[[Category:British immunologists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:University of British Columbia faculty]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|English immunologist and microbiologist}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox scientist\n| name              = Pauline Johnson\n| image             = \n| image_size        = \n| alt               = \n| caption           = \n| birth_place       = [[Yorkshire]], England\n| death_date        = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place       = \n| resting_place     = \n| resting_place_coordinates = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} -->\n| citizenship       = \n| nationality       = \n| fields            = [[Immunology]]\n| workplaces        = [[University of British Columbia]]\n| alma_mater        = [[Liverpool University]]<br/>[[University of Dundee]]<br/>[[Oxford University]]<br/>[[Salk Institute]]\n| doctoral_advisor  = \n| academic_advisors = \n| doctoral_students = \n| notable_students  = \n| known_for         = Work on lymphocyte cell surface molecules and hyaluronan \n| author_abbrev_bot = \n| author_abbrev_zoo = \n| influences        = \n| influenced        = \n| awards            = \n| signature         = <!--(filename only)-->\n| signature_alt     = \n| website           = <!-- {{URL|www.example.com}} -->\n| footnotes         = \n}}\n'''Pauline Johnson''' is an English immunologist and microbiologist at the [[University of British Columbia]].<ref name=\"UBC\" /> Her research focuses on innate and adaptive immune mechanisms \u2014 in particular, the mobility of proteins in membranes, [[lymphocyte]] cell surface molecules, [[T cell]] [[cell signaling|signalling]], [[leukocyte]] adhesion, and [[macrophage]]s in lung [[inflammation]].<ref name=\"UBC\" />\n\n==Education==\nPauline Johnson was born in [[Yorkshire]], England. She earned a BSc in biochemistry from [[Liverpool University]] in 1980, and a Ph.D from the [[University of Dundee]] in 1983.<ref name=\"UBC\" /><ref name=\"III Institute Advisory Board\">{{Cite web | url=https://cihr-irsc.gc.ca/e/50755.html#pauline_johnson |title = III Institute Advisory Board Members \u2013 Biographies - CIHR}}</ref> Her Ph.D. project was to determine the lateral and rotational mobility of membrane components measured by fluorescence recovery after photobleaching and fluorescence depletion recovery.\n<ref>{{Cite journal\n | pmid = 6170530 \n| year = 1981\n| author1 = Johnson, P. & Garland, P. B.\n| title = Depolarisation of fluorescence depletion. A microscopic method for measuring rotational diffusion of membrane proteins on the surface of a single cell\n| journal = FEBS Lett\n| volume = 132\n| issue = 2\n| pages = 252\u2013256\n| doi = 10.1016/0014-5793(81)81172-6\n}}\n</ref>\n\nShe was a post-doctoral fellow at the [[Salk Institute]] in [[California]], US under the supervision of Professor Ian Trowbridge  and at the MRC Cellular Immunology Unit at the [[University of Oxford]], U.K. under the supervision of Professor Alan F. Williams<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/Alan-Frederick-Williams.-25-May-1945-\u2013-9-April-1992-Crumpton/b4574e3cec2e7e6d5fb1b2b602446868e64b4e44|title=Alan Frederick Williams. 25 May 1945 \u2013 9 April 1992 &#124; Semantic Scholar}}</ref> before joining the faculty at the University of British Columbia in 1991.<ref name=\"III Institute Advisory Board\" />\n\n==Career and research==\nJohnson helped to establish the function of [[CD45]] as a critical protein [[tyrosine phosphatase]] in [[T cell]] activation\n<ref>{{Cite journal\n | pmid = 1314815\n| year = 1992\n| author1 = Johnson, P., Ostergaard, H. L., Wasden, C. & Trowbridge, I. S.\n| title = Mutational analysis of CD45, a leukocyte specific tyrosine phosphatase.\n| journal = Journal of Biological Chemistry\n| volume = 267\n| issue = 12\n| pages = 8035\u20138041 \n| doi = \n}}\n</ref>\nand defined the mechanisms regulating the interactions of the cell adhesion molecule [[CD44]] with the matrix component, [[hyaluronan]].<ref>{{Cite journal\n | pmid = 9794764 \n| year = 1998\n| author1 = Maiti, A., Maki, G. & Johnson P. \n| title = TNF-\u03b1 induction of CD44-mediated leukocyte adhesion by sulfation\n| journal = Science\n| volume = 282\n| issue = 5390\n| pages = 941\u2013943 \n| doi = 10.1126/science.282.5390.941\n}}\n</ref>  \n\nHer research in 2020 uses mouse models of lung disease to study the function of [[macrophages]] and the cell matrix in infection, [[inflammation]], and [[cancer]].<ref name=\"UBC\">{{Cite web|url=http://lsi.ubc.ca/person/pauline-johnson/|title=Pauline Johnson &#124; Life Sciences Institute|website=lsi.ubc.ca}}</ref>\n\nShe held an MRC Scientist Award and was Co-Director of the Infection, Inflammation and Immunity Research Group at the Life Science Institute at UBC (2003-2009).<ref name=\"III Institute Advisory Board\" /> She has served multiple times on the [[CIHR]] Immunology and Transplantation panel, including as Scientific Officer, as well as on other national and international review panels. She is a member of the CIHR III Institute Advisory Board (III institute = Inflammation, infection and immunity CIHR Institute).<ref name=\"III Institute Advisory Board\" />\n\n==Fellowships and awards==\n* Cancer Research Institute Fellowship, American Cancer Research Institute, 1987\n* MRC Scientist Award, MRC of Canada, 1999-2004\n* Women in Science Award for Community Leadership and Scientific Excellence, Minerva Foundation for B.C. Women, 2013<ref>{{cite web |title=Announcing the Honourees for Women In\u2122 Science |date=12 November 2013 |url=https://minervabc.ca/announcing-the-honourees-for-women-in-science/ |publisher=Minerva BC}}</ref>\n\n==Publications==\n*{{Cite journal\n | pmid = 6170530 \n| year = 1981\n| author1 = Johnson, P. & Garland, P. B.\n| title = Depolarisation of fluorescence depletion. A microscopic method for measuring rotational diffusion of membrane proteins on the surface of a single cell\n| journal = FEBS Lett\n| volume = 132\n| issue = 2\n| pages = 252\u2013256\n| doi = 10.1016/0014-5793(81)81172-6\n}}\n\n*{{Cite journal\n | pmid = 3092111 \n| year = 1986\n| author1 = Johnson, P. & Williams, A. F.\n| title = Striking similarities between antigen receptor J pieces and sequence in the second chain of the murine CD8 antigen\n| journal = Nature\n| volume = 323\n| issue = 6083\n| pages = 74\u201376\n| doi = 10.1038/323074a0\n| bibcode = 1986Natur.323...74J\n}}\n\n*{{Cite journal\n | pmid = 1314815\n| year = 1992\n| author1 = Johnson, P., Ostergaard, H. L., Wasden, C. & Trowbridge, I. S.\n| title = Mutational analysis of CD45, a leukocyte specific tyrosine phosphatase.\n| journal = Journal of Biological Chemistry\n| volume = 267\n| issue = 12\n| pages = 8035\u20138041 \n| doi = \n}}\n\n*{{Cite journal\n | pmid = 9794764 \n| year = 1998\n| author1 = Maiti, A., Maki, G. & Johnson P. \n| title = TNF-\u03b1 induction of CD44-mediated leukocyte adhesion by sulfation\n| journal = Science\n| volume = 282\n| issue = 5390\n| pages = 941\u2013943 \n| doi = 10.1126/science.282.5390.941\n}}\n\n*{{Cite journal\n | pmid = 21471214 \n| year = 2011\n| author1 = Ruffell, B., Poon, G.F.T., Lee, S.S.M., Brown, K.L., Tjew, S-L., Cooper. J., & Johnson, P. \n| title = Differential use of chondroitin sulfate to regulate hyaluronan binding by CD44 in inflammatory and alternatively activated macrophages\n| journal = Journal of Biological Chemistry\n| volume = 286\n| issue = 22\n| pages = 19179\u201319190\n| doi = 10.1074/jbc.M110.200790\n| pmc = 3103297\n}}\n\n*{{Cite journal\n| pmid = 25926830 \n| year = 2015\n| author1 = Lee-Sayer, S.M., Dong, Y., Arif, A.A., Olsson, M., Brown, K.L, & Johnson, P. \n| title = The where, when, how, and why of hyaluronan binding by immune cells.\n| journal = Frontiers in Immunology\n| volume = 6\n| issue = \n| pages = 150\n| doi = 10.3389/fimmu.2015.00150\n| pmc = 4396519\n}}\n\n*{{Cite journal\n | pmid = 27007678 \n| year = 2016\n| author1 = Samarakoon, A., SHIM, Y. A., Dosanjh, M, Crickmer, M., Labont\u00e8-Raymond, C., Arif, A.A. & Johnson, P.\n| title = CD45 regulates GM-CSF, retinoic acid and T cell homing in intestinal inflammation.\n| journal = Mucosal Immunology\n| volume = 9\n| issue = 6\n| pages = 1514\u20131527\n| doi = 10.1038/mi.2016.23\n}}\n\n*{{Cite journal\n | pmid = 30555472 \n| year = 2018\n| author1 = Johnson, P., Arif, AA, Lee-Sayer, S.S.M., Dong, Y.\n| title = Hyaluronan and Its Interactions With Immune Cells in the Healthy and Inflamed Lung.\n| journal = Frontiers in Immunology\n| volume = 9\n| issue = \n| pages = 2787\n| doi = 10.3389/fimmu.2018.02787\n| pmc = 6281886\n}}\n\n*{{Cite journal\n| pmid = 32082314  \n| year = 2020\n| author1 = Dong, Y., Arif, AA., Guo, J., HA, Z., Lee-Sayer, SSM., Poon, GFT., Dosanjh, M., Roskelley, C., Huan, T., Johnson, P.\n| title = CD44 loss disrupts lung lipid surfactant homeostasis and exacerbates oxidized lipid-induced lung inflammation\n| journal = Frontiers in Immunology\n| volume = 11\n| issue = \n| pages = 29\n| doi = 10.3389/fimmu.2020.00029\n| pmc = 7002364\n}}\n\n==Refrences==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.microbiology.ubc.ca/research/labs/johnson/pi Johnson Lab]\n* [https://scholar.google.ca/citations?user=HAlgVsIAAAAJ&hl=en Pauline Johnson] at Google Scholar\n\n{{authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Johnson, Pauline}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Scientists from Yorkshire]]\n[[Category:Women immunologists]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Liverpool]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Dundee]]\n[[Category:20th-century English scientists]]\n[[Category:20th-century women scientists]]\n[[Category:21st-century English scientists]]\n[[Category:21st-century women scientists]]\n[[Category:English women biologists]]\n[[Category:English microbiologists]]\n[[Category:Women microbiologists]]\n[[Category:20th-century British biologists]]\n[[Category:21st-century British biologists]]\n[[Category:English expatriates in Canada]]\n[[Category:British expatriate academics in Canada]]\n[[Category:British immunologists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:University of British Columbia faculty]]\n", "name_user": "Kj cheetham", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pauline_Johnson_(immunologist)"}
{"title_page": "Carnival Fantasy", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2015}}\n{|{{Infobox ship begin\n| display title = ital\n}}\n{{Infobox ship image\n| Ship image = 'Carnival Fantasy' Docked at Charleston (SC) July 2012.jpg\n| Ship caption = ''Carnival Fantasy''\n}}\n{{Infobox ship career\n| Hide header = \n| Ship name = *''Fantasy'' <small>(1990\u20132007)</small>\n*''Carnival Fantasy'' <small>(2007\u2013present)</small>\n| Ship flag = \n| Ship owner = [[File:Carnival Corporation house flag.svg|20px]] [[Carnival Corporation & plc]]\n| Ship operator = [[File:Carnival Corporation house flag.svg|20px]] [[Carnival Cruise Line]]\n| Ship registry = [[Panama City]], {{PAN}}<ref name=CRUCRIT>{{cite web |url= http://www.cruisecritic.com/reviews/review_page2.cfm?ShipID=6 |title=Carnival Fantasy Review |accessdate=2008-08-16 |work=Cruise Critic |publisher=The Independent Traveler, Inc. |date=1995\u20132008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080825125618/http://www.cruisecritic.com/reviews/review_page2.cfm?ShipID=6 |archivedate=August 25, 2008 |df=mdy }}</ref>\n| Ship route = Caribbean, Mexico\n| Ship ordered = \n| Ship builder = *[[Kvaerner Masa-Yards]]\n*[[Helsinki New Shipyard]]\n*[[Helsinki]], Finland\n| Ship original cost = \n| Ship yard number = 479\n| Ship way number = \n| Ship laid down = \n| Ship launched = December 9, 1988\n| Ship completed = January 27, 1990\n| Ship christened = March 1, 1990\n| Ship sponsor = [[Tellervo Koivisto]]\n| Ship acquired = \n| Ship maiden voyage = March 1, 1990\n| Ship in service = 1990<ref name= CRUCRIT/>\u2013present\n| Ship out of service = \n| Ship refit = 2013\n2016 (Funship 2.0)\n| Ship identification = *[[Call sign]]: H3GS\n*{{IMO Number|8700773}}\n*{{MMSI|353486000}}\n| Ship fate = \n| Ship status = Out of service\n| Ship notes = \n}}\n{{Infobox ship characteristics\n| Hide header = \n| Header caption = \n| Ship class = {{sclass-|Fantasy|cruise ship}}\n| Ship tonnage = *{{GT|70,367}}<ref name= CRUCRIT/>\n*{{DWT|7,180}}\n| Ship deadweight = \n| Ship length = {{cvt|855|ft|m}}\n| Ship beam = {{cvt|103|ft|m}}\n| Ship height = \n| Ship draft = {{cvt|7.80|m|ftin}}\n| Ship depth = \n| Ship decks = 10\n| Ship deck clearance = \n| Ship ramps = \n| Ship ice class = \n| Ship power = *2{{nbsp}}&times;{{nbsp}}[[Sulzer (manufacturer)|Sulzer]]-[[W\u00e4rtsil\u00e4]] 8ZAV40S\n*4{{nbsp}}&times;{{nbsp}}Sulzer-W\u00e4rtsil\u00e4 12ZAV40S\n*42,240{{nbsp}}kW (combined)\n| Ship propulsion = Two propellers\n| Ship speed = {{convert|21|kn}}\n| Ship capacity = *2,052 passengers (lower berths)\n*2,675 passengers (all berths)<ref name= CRUCRIT/>\n| Ship crew = 920\n| Ship notes = \n}}\n|}\n\n'''''Carnival Fantasy''''' (formerly '''''Fantasy''''') is the [[lead ship]] of the {{Sclass-|Fantasy|cruise ship|4}} of [[cruise ship]]s operated by American/British company [[Carnival Cruise Line]].  Built by [[Kv\u00e6rner Masa-Yards]] at its [[Helsinki New Shipyard]] in [[Helsinki]], Finland, she was [[Float-out|floated out]] on December 9, 1988, completed on January 27, 1990 <ref>{{csr|register=MSI|id=8700773|shipname=Carnival Fantasy |accessdate=8 January 2019}}</ref> and formally named on March 1, 1990, as ''Fantasy'' by [[Tellervo Koivisto]],{{sfn|Smith|2010|p=36}} wife of the then [[President of Finland]], [[Mauno Koivisto]].  During 2007, in common with all of her ''Fantasy''-class sisters, she had the prefix \"''Carnival''\" added to her name.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Dake |first1=Shawn J. |title= Cruise Ships 2007 the year in review |journal= Ocean Times |date=January 2008 |volume=12.1 |pages=2\u20138 |url= http://www.shawnandcolleen.com/sshsasocal/docs/ocean%20times%2008%20january%20v12.1.pdf |publisher= Steamship Historical Society of America: Southern California Chapter }}</ref>  She is currently the oldest vessel in the Carnival fleet.<ref name=USAToday>{{cite web |url= http://traveltips.usatoday.com/carnival-fantasy-cruise-ship-17589.html |title=Carnival Fantasy Cruise Ship |last1=Fritscher |first1=Lisa |others=Demand Media |work=USA Today |date= 2013 |accessdate= 2013-06-19}}</ref>\n\nOn March 14, 2020, Carnival announced suspension of service for all of its ships due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|COVID-19 pandemic]]. It was previously announced that service would resume on April 10, but the suspension was extended to May 11, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.clickorlando.com/news/local/2020/03/30/carnival-cruise-line-extends-suspension-amid-coronavirus-outbreak/|title=Carnival cruise line extends suspension amid coronavirus outbreak|last=Nu\u00f1ez|first=Gabriella|date=2020-03-30|website=WKMG|language=en|access-date=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n''Fantasy'' entered service in 1990 and is now the oldest cruise ship in the fleet.<ref>{{cite news |url= https://www.usatoday.com/travel/cruises/item.aspx?type=blog&ak=620000821.blog |work=USA Today |title=Most Popular |first= Gene |last= Sloan}}</ref> The ship assisted the US Coast Guard in rescuing 23 people at sea in April 2019.<ref>{{cite web |title=Coast Guard worked with Carnival cruise to rescue 23 illegal Cubans adrift for days in Gulf of Mexico |url=https://eu.usatoday.com/story/travel/cruises/2019/04/15/coast-guard-we-rescued-23-people-gulf-mexico-carnival-cruise-ship/3470830002/ |website=USA TODAY |language=en |date=Apr 15, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Areas of operation==\nUntil 1993 she cruised from the [[Port of Miami]] when she relocated to [[Port Canaveral]].\n\nIn the Fall of 2006, ''Fantasy'' was the first Carnival ship to move back to Louisiana after [[Hurricane Katrina]] with [[New Orleans]] becoming its home port, undertaking cruises to Mexico.{{citation needed|date=June 2013}}\n\n''Carnival Fantasy'' spent a month in drydock being refitted in the Fall of 2008.<ref name=EoF>{{Cite web |url= http://www.carnival.com/CMS/Articles/fantasyeof_2008.aspx |title= Carnival Fantasy to Under Full Evolutions of Fun Upgrades This Fall |date=2008-01-28 |publisher= Carnival Cruise Lines |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20090106160056/http://www.carnival.com/CMS/Articles/fantasyeof_2008.aspx |archivedate=2009-01-06}}</ref>\n\nOn September 17, 2009, Carnival announced that ''Carnival Fantasy'' would be based out of [[Mobile, Alabama]].<ref>{{cite web |publisher= AL.com |url= http://blog.al.com/live/2008/08/carnivals_fantasy_coming_to_mo.html |title= Carnival's Fantasy cruise ship coming to Mobile |accessdate= 2008-08-18 |author= Kaija Wilkinson |date=18 August 2008 |work=Press-Register }}</ref>\n\nSubsequently, she was relocated to [[Charleston, South Carolina]].\n\n''Carnival Fantasy'' was refitted in February 2016. The upgrades included being fitted with diesel engine scrubbers as well the alteration of some of the restaurants and child care areas on the ship.<ref>Carnival-news.com</ref>\n\nIn November 2016, she moved back to Mobile.<ref>{{Cite news|url= https://www.nola.com/business/index.ssf/2015/09/carnival_cruises_return_to_mob.html |title=Cruises return to Mobile with move of Carnival Fantasy ship, AL.com reports|work=NOLA.com |access-date=2018-11-30|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n''Carnival Fantasy'' was again refitted in January 2019.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://cruisefever.net/0707-updated-carnival-cruise-line-dry-dock-schedule-cruise-ships/ |title=Carnival Cruise Line's Cruise Ship Dry Dock Schedule and Upgrades |website= cruisefever.net |language= en-US |access-date= 2018-07-11}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2020,  Carnival announced that {{ship||Carnival Fascination}} will replace ''Carnival Fantasy'' at [[Port of Mobile]], effective January 2022. With no new port announced the cruise line may decommission or sell the ship at the end of its current sailings.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://cruiseradio.net/carnival-cruise-line-moves-fantasy-out-of-mobile/|title=Carnival Cruise Line Moves Fantasy Out of Mobile|last=Parker|first=Doug|date=|website=cruiseradio.net|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-18}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n\n=== Notes ===\n{{Reflist}}\n\n=== Bibliography ===\n* {{Saunders-Giants of the Seas}}\n* {{Smith-Cruise Ships-2010}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|IMO 8700773}}\n* [http://www.carnival.com/cruise-ships/carnival-fantasy.aspx Official website]\n\n{{Carnival Cruise Line}}\n\n[[Category:Ships built in Helsinki]]\n[[Category:Ships of Carnival Cruise Line|Fantasy]]\n[[Category:1990 ships]]\n[[Category:Cruise ships]]\n[[Category:Fantasy-class cruise ships|Fantasy]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2015}}\n{|{{Infobox ship begin\n| display title = ital\n}}\n{{Infobox ship image\n| Ship image = 'Carnival Fantasy' Docked at Charleston (SC) July 2012.jpg\n| Ship caption = ''Carnival Fantasy''\n}}\n{{Infobox ship career\n| Hide header = \n| Ship name = *''Fantasy'' <small>(1990\u20132007)</small>\n*''Carnival Fantasy'' <small>(2007\u2013present)</small>\n| Ship flag = \n| Ship owner = [[File:Carnival Corporation house flag.svg|20px]] [[Carnival Corporation & plc]]\n| Ship operator = [[File:Carnival Corporation house flag.svg|20px]] [[Carnival Cruise Line]]\n| Ship registry = [[Panama City]], {{PAN}}<ref name=CRUCRIT>{{cite web |url= http://www.cruisecritic.com/reviews/review_page2.cfm?ShipID=6 |title=Carnival Fantasy Review |accessdate=2008-08-16 |work=Cruise Critic |publisher=The Independent Traveler, Inc. |date=1995\u20132008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20080825125618/http://www.cruisecritic.com/reviews/review_page2.cfm?ShipID=6 |archivedate=August 25, 2008 |df=mdy }}</ref>\n| Ship route = Caribbean, Mexico\n| Ship ordered = \n| Ship builder = *[[Kvaerner Masa-Yards]]\n*[[Helsinki New Shipyard]]\n*[[Helsinki]], Finland\n| Ship original cost = \n| Ship yard number = 479\n| Ship way number = \n| Ship laid down = \n| Ship launched = December 9, 1988\n| Ship completed = January 27, 1990\n| Ship christened = March 1, 1990\n| Ship sponsor = [[Tellervo Koivisto]]\n| Ship acquired = \n| Ship maiden voyage = March 1, 1990\