xt-align:left;\" | [[Rie Tanaka]] || style=\"text-align:left;\" | Allegra Clark\n|-\n| Sierokarte || {{Nihongo|\u30b7\u30a7\u30ed\u30ab\u30eb\u30c6|Sherokarute}}|| style=\"text-align:center;\" |  || style=\"text-align:center;\" | {{y}} || style=\"text-align:center;\" |  || style=\"text-align:center;\" |  || style=\"text-align:left;\" | [[Emiri Kato]] || style=\"text-align:left;\" | Faye Mata\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;|'''Total'''|| style=\"text-align:center;|'''28'''|| style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''12'''|| style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''11'''|| style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''5''' || style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''1''' || style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''28''' || style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''24'''\n|}\n\n* {{note|Chaos Bringer|Chaos Bringer}} Originally listed as {{Nihongo|Chaos Bringer|\u9ed2\u8863\u306e\u7537|Kokui no otoko|Hooded Figure}}. Also unlockable after finishing RPG Mode after his DLC release.\n* {{note|Cameo|Cameo}} Represents characters who made cameos or are part playable character's move lists.\n\n==Reception==\n{{Video game reviews\n| MC = PS4: 78/100<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-4/granblue-fantasy-versus |title=Granblue Fantasy Versus for PlayStation 4 Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |publisher=[[CBS Interactive]] |accessdate=March 27, 2020}}</ref>\n| Destruct = 7.5/10<ref name=\"Destruct\">{{cite web|url=https://www.destructoid.com/review-granblue-fantasy-versus-581157.phtml|title=Granblue Fantasy Versus Review|date=March 2, 2020|first=Chris|last=Carter|accessdate=March 4, 2020}}</ref>\n| Fam = 34/40<ref name=\"Fam\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gematsu.com/2020/01/famitsu-review-scores-issue-1626|title=Famitsu Review Scores: Issue 1626|first=Sal|last=Romano|work=Gematsu|date=January 29, 2020|accessdate=March 4, 2020}}</ref>\n| GSpot = 7/10<ref name=\"GSpot\">{{cite web|url=https://www.gamespot.com/reviews/granblue-fantasy-versus-review-fighting-fantasy/1900-6417420/|title=Gamespot Granblue Fantasy Versus Review|first=Tamoor|last=Hussain|date=March 2, 2019|accessdate=March 4, 2020}}</ref>\n| HCG = {{rating|4.5|5}}<ref name=\"HCG\">{{cite web|url=https://hardcoregamer.com/2020/03/02/review-granblue-fantasy-versus/368651/|title=Review:Granblue Fantasy Versus|first=Kirstin|last=Swalley|date=September 26, 2019|accessdate=February 21, 2020}}</ref>\n| IGN = 8/10<ref name=\"IGN\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/granblue-fantasy-versus-review|title=IGN Granblue Fantasy Versus Review|date=February 11, 2020|accessdate=March 4, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\nThe game received \"generally favorable reviews\" according to review aggregator [[Metacritic]]. ''[[IGN]]'' gave the game an 8 out of 10 calling it an another excellent addition to the ArcSys family.\n\n=== Sales ===\nAccording to Famitsu, ''Granblue Fantasy Versus'' debuted at #1 in Japan with a total of 86,248 copies sold during its launch week.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gematsu.com/2020/02/famitsu-sales-2-3-20-2-9-20|title=Famitsu Sales: 2/3/20 \u2013 2/9/20 [Update]|date=2020-02-12|website=Gematsu|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref> The game also debuted at #2 in Taiwan and #4 in South Korea according to Media Create.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gnn.gamer.com.tw/detail.php?sn=192816|title=MediaCreate 2 \u6708 3 \u65e5\uff5e2 \u6708 9 \u65e5\u4e00\u9031\u92b7\u552e\u6392\u884c\u699c \u300a\u78a7\u85cd\u5e7b\u60f3 Versus\u300b\u596a\u65e5\u53f0\u96d9\u51a0|last=\u5df4\u54c8\u59c6\u7279|website=\u5df4\u54c8\u59c6\u7279\u96fb\u73a9\u8cc7\u8a0a\u7ad9|access-date=2020-02-17}}</ref>\n\n{{clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://granbluefantasyvs.com/}}\n\n{{Cygames}}\n\n[[Category:Arc System Works games]]\n[[Category:Esports games]]\n[[Category:Fantasy video games]]\n[[Category:Fiction about magic]]\n[[Category:Fiction about monsters]]\n[[Category:Fighting games]]\n[[Category:Fighting games used at the Evolution Championship Series tournament]]\n[[Category:Granblue Fantasy]]\n[[Category:Japan-exclusive video games]]\n[[Category:Multiplayer video games]]\n[[Category:PlayStation 4 games]]\n[[Category:Single-player video games]]\n[[Category:Video games based on Arthurian legend]]\n[[Category:Video games developed in Japan]]\n[[Category:Video games featuring female protagonists]]\n[[Category:Video games featuring protagonists of selectable gender]]\n[[Category:Windows games]]\n[[Category:Unreal Engine games]]\n\n{{Fighting-videogame-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{Infobox video game\n| collapsible = \n| state = \n| italic title = \n| title = Granblue Fantasy Versus\n| image = Granblue Fantasy Versus logo.png\n| alt = \n| caption = \n| developer = [[Arc System Works]]\n| publisher = {{vgrelease|JP|[[Cygames]]|AS|[[Square Enix]], [[Sega]]|NA|[[Xseed Games]]|EU|[[Marvelous (company)|Marvelous]]}}\n| series = [[Granblue Fantasy]]\n| engine = [[Unreal Engine 4]]<ref>{{cite web |title=The 'Granblue Fantasy' Series Has Some Interesting New Games On The Way |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/olliebarder/2018/12/16/the-granblue-fantasy-series-has-some-interesting-new-games-on-the-way/ |website=Forbes |accessdate=26 February 2019}}</ref>\n| platforms = [[PlayStation 4]], [[Microsoft Windows]]\n| released = '''PlayStation 4'''<br>{{vgr|AS|February 6, 2020|NA|March 3, 2020|EU|March 27, 2020}}'''Microsoft Windows'''<br>{{vgr|WW|March 13, 2020}}\n| genre = [[Fighting game|Fighting]], [[Role-playing video game|role-playing game]]\n| modes = \n| director = Tetsuya Fukuhara\n| producer = Yuito Kimura\n| designer = Kazuto Sekine\n| programmer = Masashige Kazuhito\n| artist = {{unbulleted list|Hideo Minaba|Hideaki Sawada}}\n| writer = {{unbulleted list|Kyohei Terashima|Shingo Noguchi|Tetsuya Fukuhara}}\n| composer = {{unbulleted list|Tsutomu Narita|Yasunori Nishiki|Hidenori Maezawa|Nao Tokisawa|Azusa Chiba}}\n}}\n\n'''''Granblue Fantasy Versus''''' is a 2.5D [[fighting game]] developed by [[Arc System Works]] for the [[PlayStation 4]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://versus.granbluefantasy.jp/?lang=en|title=Granblue Fantasy: Versus {{!}} Cygames|website=Granblue Fantasy: Versus {{!}} Cygames|language=ja|access-date=2019-09-17}}</ref><ref name=\"Gematsu1\">{{citation|title = Arc System Works-developed Granblue Fantasy Versus announced for PS4 | url = https://gematsu.com/2018/12/arc-system-works-developed-granblue-fantasy-versus-announced-for-ps4 | first = Sal | last = Romano | date = 15 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://twinfinite.net/2018/12/granblue-fantasy-versus-announced/ | title=Granblue Fantasy Versus for PS4 by Arc System Works Announced| date=2018-12-15}}</ref> It is based on the [[role-playing video game]] ''[[Granblue Fantasy]]'', and it was released in Japan and Asia by [[Cygames]], [[Square Enix]], and [[Sega]] respectively on February 6, 2020, and North America by [[Marvelous (company)|Marvelous]]' [[Xseed Games]] on March 3, 2020.<ref name=\"Release Date\">{{citation|title = Granblue Fantasy: Versus adds Zeta and Vaseraga + Release Date | url = https://gematsu.com/2019/10/granblue-fantasy-versus-adds-zeta-vaseraga-japanese-box-art | first = Sal | last = Romano | date = 13 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gematsu.com/2019/06/granblue-fantasy-versus-published-by-xseed-games-in-north-america|title=Granblue Fantasy: Versus published by XSEED Games in North America|date=June 7, 2019}}</ref><ref>https://twitter.com/XSEEDGames/status/1223313625156411392</ref> [[Microsoft Windows]] release was officially announced for March 13, 2020, to commemorate the 6th anniversary of the series.<ref>https://twitter.com/gbvs_official/status/1232968809314570241</ref>\n\n==Gameplay==\n''Granblue Fantasy Versus'' is mainly a fighting game where the goal is to eliminate the opponent by using a combination of attacks to empty their character's life bar enough times to win the match.  Each character has special abilities called \"Skybound Arts,\"<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=https://versus.granbluefantasy.jp/?lang=en|title=Granblue Fantasy: Versus &#124; Cygames|website=Granblue Fantasy: Versus &#124; Cygames}}</ref> which correspond to skills that the character is able to use in the main ''[[Granblue Fantasy]]'' game. In an attempt to make the game more accessible to new players, each Skybound Arts can be triggered with a simple button press, but the player will have to wait for a short [[cooldown]] period before they can use it again.  However, if the player uses a more advanced combination of movement and button presses to launch the attack, the cooldown time on the skill will be shortened.\n\nThe game also contains a story mode. Unlike the main fighting game mode, the story mode is more of a side-scrolling, [[beat-'em up]], [[action role-playing game]]. The story mode includes exclusive bosses and minions to battle, setting weapon grids, and a co-op mode.<ref name=\"Granblue Extra Fes 2019\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.eventhubs.com/news/2019/jul/20/granblue-fantasy-versus-will-reportedly-receive-ton-new-information-granblue-extra-fes-2019-august-3/|title=Granblue Fantasy Versus will reportedly receive a ton of new information at Granblue Extra Fes 2019 on August 3|first=Dakota 'DarkHorse'|last=Hills|date=July 20, 2019|website=EventHubs}}</ref>\n\n==Characters==\n<!-- Do not add Erika Harlacher yet. It is unknown if she reprises her role as Djeeta -->\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! width=75px | Character\n! style=\"text-align:center; width:180px;\"|Name JP\n! style=\"text-align:center; width:20px;\"|Base Roster<br><ref name=\"Gematsu2\">{{citation|title = Granblue Fantasy: Versus adds Lowain | url = https://gematsu.com/2019/03/granblue-fantasy-versus-adds-lowain | first = Sal | last = Romano | date = 9 March 2019}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"Gematsu3\">{{citation|title =  Granblue Fantasy: Versus adds Ladiva | url = https://gematsu.com/2019/05/granblue-fantasy-versus-adds-ladiva | first = Sal | last = Romano |